    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">1. The service</h2>
    <p>
        CalCrony provides event scheduling, RSVPs, reminders, polls, calendar feeds, and related
        features for Discord servers. You interact with it through Discord slash commands and message
        components, and optionally through this web app after signing in with Discord. By adding the
        bot to a server or signing in, you accept these terms. If you add the bot to a server, you're
        responsible for ensuring that server's members are okay with the data handling described in
        the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">2. Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Follow <a href="https://discord.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord's Terms of
            Service</a> and Community Guidelines — CalCrony operates inside Discord and doesn't exempt
            you from its rules.</li>
        <li>Don't use CalCrony to spam, harass, or automate abuse (e.g., mass-pinging via notification
            mentions or attendee roles).</li>
        <li>Don't probe, overload, or attempt to bypass the service's authentication.</li>
        <li>Content you put into events, polls, templates, and reminders is yours; you're responsible
            for it. Server managers and event creators can edit or delete content per the permission
            rules built into the service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">3. Google Calendar features</h2>
    <p>
        Linking a Google Calendar is optional and grants CalCrony read-only free/busy access only.
        Your use of those features is also subject to Google's terms. You can disconnect at any time
        (<code>/calendar disconnect</code> or My settings), which deletes the stored tokens.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Availability &amp; changes</h2>
    <p>
        This is a hobby-scale, best-effort service: no uptime guarantee, no SLA. Features may change,
        and the service may be modified, interrupted, or discontinued at any time. Notable changes
        ship through the project's public release notes.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Termination</h2>
    <p>
        We may remove the bot from a server or disable access that violates these terms or Discord's.
        You can stop using the service at any time by kicking the bot from your server; see the
        Privacy Policy for what happens to data afterward.
    </p>

